                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On April 21, 1953, Ambassador Douglas Dillon at Paris wrote a brief note to Under
                    Secretary of State Walter Bedell Smith discussing Cohn’s and Schine’s return
                    visit to France. In the letter, Ambassador Dillon stated, in part, that “some
                    information on budgets” was given to Cohn, and that he “was critical of the
                    operation in Germany, particularly of the spending of money to finance overtly
                    the publication of a newspaper.” (711.52/4–2153)</p>
            </div>
